messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path:
  /cms/user

- All HTTP methods acceptable: No

- HEAD: False
- POST: False
- OPTIONS: False
- TRACE: False
- GET: False
- PUT: True
- DELETE: False
- PATCH: False

Explanation:
- The app registers the CMS blueprint under the prefix "/cms" (app/__init__.py: app.register_blueprint(create_cms(), url_prefix="/cms")).
- Inside app/api/cms/__init__.py the user blueprint (user_api) is registered at url_prefix="/user".
- In app/api/cms/user.py there is a route decorated as @user_api.route("", methods=["PUT"]) â€” an empty route string attaches to the blueprint prefix. Combining the prefixes yields the full path "/cms" + "/user" + "" -> "/cms/user".
- That specific route declares methods=["PUT"], so only PUT is acceptable for the /cms/user endpoint based strictly on the code. Other HTTP methods are not declared for this route (the file does define other routes under /cms/user/* for login, register, captcha, etc., but those are different endpoints).
